      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__libvlc__log_1ga6b95ea7c2e62c7b69a9bc79aafd8c6bc" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>LIBVLC_API void</type>
        <definition>LIBVLC_API void libvlc_log_unset</definition>
        <argsstring>(libvlc_instance_t *p_instance)</argsstring>
        <name>libvlc_log_unset</name>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="group__libvlc__core_1ga316d739a80da4678206c79f4d6c2e284" kindref="member">libvlc_instance_t</ref> *</type>
          <declname>p_instance</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Unsets the logging callback.</para>
<para>This function deregisters the logging callback for a LibVLC instance. This is rarely needed as the callback is implicitly unset when the instance is destroyed.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>This function will wait for any pending callbacks invocation to complete (causing a deadlock if called from within the callback).</para>
</simplesect>
<parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>p_instance</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>libvlc instance </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="version"><para>LibVLC 2.1.0 or later </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
